From: tawc
Origin: own

Replace the AOSP-only `nativewindow` Rust crate path in
src/gfxstream.rs's PLATFORM_AHB export branch with an embedder-
installed callback hook. The nativewindow crate is the Rust binding
to libnativewindow.so vendor APIs (specifically
AHardwareBuffer_getNativeHandle), only published inside AOSP, so
rutabaga doesn't build outside AOSP with the gfxstream feature.

The hook is what lets the tawc compositor satisfy kumquat's
RESOURCE_CREATE_BLOB protocol contract (the response is *required*
to ship one fd via SCM_RIGHTS for every PLATFORM_AHB). The
compositor's registered callback dlsym's
`AHardwareBuffer_getNativeHandle` out of `libnativewindow.so`,
walks the handle, dups out the AHB's backing dmabuf fd, and
returns it. The wrapper here boxes that into a MesaHandle of type
MEM_DMABUF so the kumquat layer can ship it via SCM_RIGHTS unchanged.

For host-visible Vulkan memory the chroot mmaps the fd to read/
write into the host VkBuffer. For DEVICE_LOCAL allocations
(swapchain images, depth buffers) the chroot ignores the fd; the
swapchain image is named separately by colorbuffer_id over the
custom `tawc_gfxstream` Wayland protocol (see
notes/gfxstream-bridge.md "WSI plan: custom Vulkan WSI"). Either
way the contract on this branch is identical — fd shipped, kind
of fd determined by what the AHB happens to back.

With no callback set, the branch falls back to InvalidResourceId --
that's the right answer for the bin'd `kumquat` binary, which has
no AHB consumer wired up.

